Sentencas: This work develops a novel perovskite Sr2FeNi0.35Mo0.65O6-delta (SFN0.35M) simultaneously using as a fuel electrode and oxygen electrode in a reversible solid oxide cell (RSOC).
Titulo: Ni-Substituted Sr2FeMoO6-δ as an Electrode Material for Symmetrical and Reversible Solid-Oxide Cells

Sentencas: SFN0.35M shows outstanding electrocatalytic activity for hydrogen oxidation, hydrogen evolution, oxygen reduction, and oxygen evolution.
Titulo: Ni-Substituted Sr2FeMoO6-δ as an Electrode Material for Symmetrical and Reversible Solid-Oxide Cells

Sentencas: In situ exsolution and dissolution of Fe-Ni alloy nanoparticles in SFN0.35M is revealed.
Titulo: Ni-Substituted Sr2FeMoO6-δ as an Electrode Material for Symmetrical and Reversible Solid-Oxide Cells

Sentencas: In a reducing atmosphere, SFN0.35M shows in situ exsolution of Fe-Ni alloy nanoparticles, and then the Fe-Ni alloy is reoxidized into SFN0.35M while converting into an oxidizing atmosphere.
Titulo: Ni-Substituted Sr2FeMoO6-δ as an Electrode Material for Symmetrical and Reversible Solid-Oxide Cells

Sentencas: The polarization resistances of SFN0.35M electrode are 0.043 Omega cm(2) in 20% O-2-N-2 and 0.064 Omega cm(2) in H-2 at 850 degree celsius.
Titulo: Ni-Substituted Sr2FeMoO6-δ as an Electrode Material for Symmetrical and Reversible Solid-Oxide Cells

Sentencas: Moreover, symmetric fuel cells using the SFN0.35M electrode achieves a maximum power density of 0.501 W cm(-2) at 850 degrees C in H-2 fuel, while the symmetric electrolysis cell has an electrolysis current density of 0.794 A cm(-2) at 1.29 V in 90%
Titulo: Ni-Substituted Sr2FeMoO6-δ as an Electrode Material for Symmetrical and Reversible Solid-Oxide Cells
Ni-Substituted Sr2FeMoO6-δ as an Electrode Material for Symmetrical and Reversible Solid-Oxide Cells

Sentencas: It is the first time we demonstrate that the cell voltage of symmetrical cell at 0.5 A cm(-2) in the fuel cell mode and -0.5 A cm(-2) in the electrolysis cell mode can be fully recovered in 10 electrode alternating cycles and therefore demonstrate the possibility that SFN0.35M can be used in a fully symmetric RSOC stack with electrode alternating functions.
Titulo: Ni-Substituted Sr2FeMoO6-δ as an Electrode Material for Symmetrical and Reversible Solid-Oxide Cells
